The judiciary in Kogi State yesterday approached the State High Court sitting in Koton-Karfe seeking nullification of the April 2 resolution ofÂ  the House of Assembly recommending the removal of the Chief Judge, Justice Nasir Ajanah. The motion was filed by Adegboyega Awomolo (SAN) leading 11 other lawyers, including five Senior Advocates of Nigeria on behalf of the claimants/applicants, Justice Ajanah and the Chief Registrar of the state High Court, Alhaji Yahaya Adamu. Awomolo said the motion was brought pursuant to Order 11, Rules 1 and 2 of Kogi State High Court (Civil Procedure) Rules, 2006 to counter the action of the assembly in defying the court order in the impasse between the legislature and the executive. Joined in the motion were the assembly, Speaker Bello Hassan Abdullahi, the chairman of the ad hoc committee, Governor Yahaya Bello and the Attorney-General the state. Kogi Judiciary asks court to nullify assembly's resolution on CJ's removal Kogi govt, judiciary rift: Bello, lawmakers seek out-of-court settlement Kogi CJ : Judiciary workers threaten nationwide strike